results.name: An involution of nonnegative integers: signature permutation of a nonrecursive Catalan automorphism which swaps the sides of a binary tree if the left subtree of either the left or right hand side toplevel subtree is not empty and otherwise keeps the binary tree intact.
comment: This automorphism effects the following transformation on the unlabeled rooted plane binary trees (letters A, B, C and D refer to arbitrary subtrees located on those nodes.)
link: A. Karttunen, Prolog-program which illustrates the construction of this and other similar nonrecursive Catalan automorphisms.
Index entries for signature-permutations of Catalan automorphisms
program: (Scheme function, destructive implementation of this automorphism acting on S-expressions:) (define (*A123492! s) (cond ((null? s) s) ((and (pair? (cdr s)) (pair? (cadr s))) (*A069770! s)) ((and (pair? (car s)) (pair? (caar s))) (*A069770! s))) s)
